⟦ Effect ordering stays source-ordered.

  `first()` is initiated before `second()`, even though the runtime may overlap
  their resolution before the final record is observed.
⟧

t Pair={a:String,b:String}

λfirst()=>!IO String="first"

λmain()=>!IO Pair={a:first(),b:second()}

λsecond()=>!IO String="second"
